, 
<figureCitation id="136D999CD11449747A6AC0B9FCDE3676" box="[788,805,502,528]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1818,1844]" captionTargetBox="[259,1328,265,1777]" captionTargetId="figure-17@14.[259,1328,265,1777]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 4. Pantolyta augustinusii sp. nov. A–D. Holotype (NHMD-300829). A. Habitus in dorsal view. B. Head in frontal view. C. Detail of the anterior mesosoma in dorsal view. D. Gaster and petiole in lateral view.E. Paratype (NHMD-608391), habitus in lateral view.F. Paratype (NHMD-608406), habitus in lateral view. G. Paratype (NHMD-608412), habitus in lateral view. H. Paratype (NHMD-608404), habitus in dorsal view. Abbreviations: asp = anterior scutellar pit; fe = flagellomere emargination; t = toruli. Scale bars: A–B, D–H = 1 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468189/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="70">4</figureCitation>
