<paragraph id="8BE98519D114497479C3C470FC573229" blockId="13.[188,1400,1308,1616]" pageId="13" pageNumber="70">
BODY. BL 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11449747842C470FEB6313F" bold="true" box="[316,333,1343,1369]" pageId="13" pageNumber="70">=</emphasis>
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD1144974782AC470FDF8313F" box="[340,515,1343,1370]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.99" metricValueMax="3.47" metricValueMin="2.51" pageId="13" pageNumber="70" unit="mm" value="2.99" valueMax="3.47" valueMin="2.51">2.51–3.47 mm</quantity>
. Head subtriangular in frontal view (HeL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11449747D71C470FB3B313F" box="[1039,1216,1343,1369]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.35" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="3.9" pageId="13" pageNumber="70" unit="mm" value="0.435" valueMax="0.48" valueMin="0.39">0.39–0.48 mm</quantity>
); eye large, not pubescent; several hairs on frons; antennae inserted on distinct but not prominent shelf; toruli well developed, as long as one sixth of scape length from base to apex, separated by distinct cleft; antennae bearing numerous short setae; scape almost six times as long as wide; pedicel slightly longer than wide; flagellomeres elongate, cylindrical; F1 half of scape length, with an indistinct emargination basally; F2–F11 subequal in length; F12 longer and tapering at apex (antennomeres length of 
<typeStatus id="54ED3BBBD11449747DD2C4A0FAED326F" box="[1196,1302,1519,1545]" pageId="13" pageNumber="70">holotype</typeStatus>
, in mm: Sc-0.38; P-0.08; F1-0.21; F2-0.19; F3-0.19; F4-0.19; F5-0.19; F6-0.20; F7-0.19; F8-0.20; F9-0.21; F10- 0.21; F11-0.21; F12-0.23); mandibles short, not forming a beak.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D114497479C3C738FA9033AB" blockId="13.[189,1400,1655,1998]" pageId="13" pageNumber="70">
MESOSOMA. Shorter than metasoma (MsL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11449747BB4C738FC8032F7" box="[714,891,1655,1681]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.095" metricValueMax="1.29" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="13" pageNumber="70" unit="mm" value="1.095" valueMax="1.29" valueMin="0.9">0.90–1.29 mm</quantity>
); pronotum visible in dorsal view; epomia present as a simple keel; pronotal shoulders rounded; mesoscutum smooth, bearing long hairs; notauli deeply impressed, anteriorly converging towards scutellum, posteriorly parallel just before transscutal sulcus; anterior scutellar pit large, deep; scutellum without posterior scutellar pits; mesopleuron bare, mesopleural pit present; propodeum with median keel simple. Fore wing hyaline, extending far beyond metasoma (FwL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD114497478E4C668FDB23327" box="[410,585,1831,1858]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.07" metricValueMax="3.54" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="13" pageNumber="70" unit="mm" value="3.07" valueMax="3.54" valueMin="2.6">2.60–3.54 mm</quantity>
), covered with micropubescence; C, Sc+R, M+Cu, basal vein and Cu pigmented; basal and costal cells closed; marginal vein slightly widened, about two thirds as long as its distance from basal vein and twice as long as r-rs; postmarginal vein pigmented, extending slightly beyond radial cell; radial cell closed; Rs tubular distally to r-rs, nebulous proximally; M inconspicuous towards apex. Legs slender, hind femur slightly thicker; tibial spur formula 1-2-2; tarsal claws simple.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF29D591D117497779C3C655FCED3383" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468189" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6468189" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468189/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="71" startId="14.[189,232,1818,1844]" targetBox="[259,1328,265,1777]" targetPageId="14">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D117497779C3C655FCED3383" blockId="14.[187,1401,1818,2021]" pageId="14" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="B922590BD117497779C3C655FEF53352" bold="true" box="[189,270,1818,1844]" pageId="14" pageNumber="71">Fig. 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11749777867C655FDDF3352" authority="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen, 2022" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[281,548,1818,1844]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="augustinusii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11749777867C655FDDF3352" box="[281,548,1818,1844]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="71">Pantolyta augustinusii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D11749777B51C654FD773353" box="[559,652,1819,1845]" pageId="14" pageNumber="71" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis id="B922590BD11749777BE8C655FD343352" bold="true" box="[662,719,1818,1844]" pageId="14" pageNumber="71">A–D</emphasis>
. Holotype (NHMD-300829). 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11749777D47C655FBB53352" bold="true" box="[1081,1102,1818,1844]" pageId="14" pageNumber="71">A</emphasis>
. Habitus in dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD117497779C3C671FF2A333E" bold="true" box="[189,209,1854,1880]" pageId="14" pageNumber="71">B</emphasis>
. Head in frontal view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11749777892C672FE043331" bold="true" box="[492,511,1853,1879]" pageId="14" pageNumber="71">C</emphasis>
. Detail of the anterior mesosoma in dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11749777D26C671FB90333E" bold="true" box="[1112,1131,1854,1880]" pageId="14" pageNumber="71">D</emphasis>
. Gaster and petiole in lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11749777832C62EFE9B331D" bold="true" box="[332,352,1889,1915]" pageId="14" pageNumber="71">E</emphasis>
. Paratype (NHMD-608391), habitus in lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11749777AC4C62EFC37331D" bold="true" box="[954,972,1889,1915]" pageId="14" pageNumber="71">F</emphasis>
. Paratype (NHMD-608406), habitus in lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11749777804C6CBFE7433F8" bold="true" box="[378,399,1924,1950]" pageId="14" pageNumber="71">G</emphasis>
. Paratype (NHMD-608412), habitus in lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11749777D75C6CBFBDB33F8" bold="true" box="[1035,1056,1924,1950]" pageId="14" pageNumber="71">H</emphasis>
. Paratype (NHMD-608404), habitus in dorsal view. Abbreviations: asp = anterior scutellar pit; fe = flagellomere emargination; t = toruli. Scale bars: A–B, D–H = 1 mm; C = 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D116497679C3C046FAC7350F" blockId="15.[188,1398,265,362]" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">
METASOMA. Petiole cylindrical, 2.4 times as long as its middle width (PtL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11649767D55C046FB233545" box="[1067,1240,265,291]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" unit="mm" value="0.32" valueMax="0.37" valueMin="0.27">0.27–0.37 mm</quantity>
; PtW = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11649767C48C046FED33521" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" unit="mm" value="0.13" valueMax="0.15" valueMin="0.11">0.11– 0.15 mm</quantity>
), with longitudinal ribs, long hairs laterally and ventrally; gaster fusiform (GL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11649767DB9C063FA893521" box="[1223,1394,300,327]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.115" metricValueMax="1.33" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" unit="mm" value="1.115" valueMax="1.33" valueMin="0.9">0.90–1.33 mm</quantity>
; GH = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD1164976787BC000FE49350C" box="[261,434,335,362]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="5.8" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" unit="mm" value="0.5" valueMax="0.58" valueMin="0.42">0.42–0.58 mm</quantity>
), smooth; T2 longest, narrowing toward petiole; other segments much shorter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11649767994C0DEFEBE35CD" blockId="15.[189,325,401,462]" box="[234,325,401,427]" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11649767994C0DEFEBE35CD" bold="true" box="[234,325,401,427]" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">Female</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D116497679C3C0FBFEC235A8" blockId="15.[189,325,401,462]" box="[189,313,436,462]" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34CD692D116497679C3C0BAFBB030F2" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D116497679C3C0BAFEBF3669" blockId="15.[189,324,501,527]" box="[189,324,501,527]" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">
<heading id="D0A13275D116497679C3C0BAFEBF3669" bold="true" box="[189,324,501,527]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B922590BD116497679C3C0BAFEBF3669" bold="true" box="[189,324,501,527]" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">Comments</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D116497679C3C36BFBB030F2" blockId="15.[188,1402,548,1172]" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">
Using 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11649767870C36BFE3F3659" author="Nixon G. E. J." box="[270,452,548,575]" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref15689" refString="Nixon G. E. J. 1957. Hymenoptera, Proctotrupoidea, Diapriidae, subfamily Belytinae. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 8 (dii): 1 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.5281 / zenodo. 23920" type="journal article" year="1957">Nixon’s (1957)</bibRefCitation>
key to the genera of 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11649767BAFC36BFCBF3658" authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1856" box="[721,836,548,574]" class="Insecta" family="Belytinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Belytinae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11649767A2DC36BFBA43658" authority="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen, 2022" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[851,1119,548,574]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="augustinusii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11649767A2DC36BFBA43658" box="[851,1119,548,574]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">Pantolyta augustinusii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D11649767D14C36AFB323659" box="[1130,1225,549,575]" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
keys out near 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD116497679C3C307FE1B3604" authority="Forster, 1856" authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1856" box="[189,480,583,610]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Acropiesta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD116497679C3C307FEC03604" box="[189,315,584,610]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">Acropiesta</emphasis>
Förster, 1856
</taxonomicName>
because of the following characters: notauli present, second flagellomere not modified; scutellum without foveae; mandibles not forming a beak; marginal vein shorter than both radial cell and its distance from basal vein; pronotum with reduced epomia; large tergite markedly tapering towards petiole. 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD1164976788AC3FEFCFB36AD" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[500,768,689,715]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="augustinusii">
<emphasis id="B922590BD1164976788AC3FEFCFB36AD" box="[500,768,689,715]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">Pantolyta augustinusii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
especially share with 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11649767D68C3FEFB6F36AD" authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1856" box="[1046,1172,689,715]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Acropiesta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11649767D68C3FEFB6F36AD" box="[1046,1172,689,715]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">Acropiesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the antennal shelf prominent with toruli separated by a furrow, the 14-segmented antennae with F1 modified, the pronotal shoulders rounded, the notauli complete, the anterior scutellar pit large and quadrate, the propodeum with median keel simple, the fore wing venation with C, Sc+R, M+Cu, Rs, basal and marginal vein tubular, the petiole cylindrical (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11649767B4DC272FD36373E" author="Macek J." box="[563,717,829,856]" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" pagination="21 - 42" refId="ref15472" refString="Macek J. 1998. Revision of European species of Acropiesta (Hymenoptera: Diapriidae) with description of new species. Folia Heyrovskyana 6: 21 - 42." type="journal article" year="1998">Macek 1998</bibRefCitation>
). However, due to their close similarities, 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11649767DB4C271FAB3373E" authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1856" box="[1226,1352,830,856]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Acropiesta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11649767DB4C271FAB3373E" box="[1226,1352,830,856]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">Acropiesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has recently been synonymized under 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11649767B24C22EFD37371D" authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1856" box="[602,716,865,891]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11649767B24C22EFD37371D" box="[602,716,865,891]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">Pantolyta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11649767B80C22EFB94371D" author="Chemyreva V. G. &amp; Kolyada V. A." box="[766,1135,865,891]" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" pagination="137 - 162" refId="ref14407" refString="Chemyreva V. G. &amp; Kolyada V. A. 2021. Taxonomy of the genera Acropiesta, Anommatium, Erasikea and Pantolyta (Diapriidae: Belytinae) with review of species occurring in Russia. Zoosystemica Rossica 30: 137 - 162. https: // doi. org / 10.31610 / zsr / 2021.30.1.137" type="journal article" year="2021">Chemyreva &amp; Kolyada (2021)</bibRefCitation>
. Four other 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11649767C7AC22EFEE937F8" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11649767C7AC22EFA8D371D" box="[1284,1398,865,891]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">Pantolyta</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
are present in Baltic amber, two having been described under 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11649767AA2C2CBFBA137F8" authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1856" box="[988,1114,900,926]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Acropiesta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11649767AA2C2CBFBA137F8" box="[988,1114,900,926]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">Acropiesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and not duly transferred by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11649767998C2E8FD9837A7" author="Chemyreva V. G. &amp; Kolyada V. A." box="[230,611,935,961]" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" pagination="137 - 162" refId="ref14407" refString="Chemyreva V. G. &amp; Kolyada V. A. 2021. Taxonomy of the genera Acropiesta, Anommatium, Erasikea and Pantolyta (Diapriidae: Belytinae) with review of species occurring in Russia. Zoosystemica Rossica 30: 137 - 162. https: // doi. org / 10.31610 / zsr / 2021.30.1.137" type="journal article" year="2021">Chemyreva &amp; Kolyada (2021)</bibRefCitation>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11649767B0BC2E8FC1D37A7" authority="Buhl, 1999" authorityName="Buhl" authorityYear="1999" box="[629,998,935,961]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antiqua">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11649767B0BC2E8FCB437A7" box="[629,847,935,961]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">Pantolyta antiqua</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11649767A22C2E8FC1D37A7" author="Buhl P. N." box="[860,998,935,961]" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" pagination="187 - 189" refId="ref14061" refString="Buhl P. N. 1999. On a collection of Hymenoptera in Baltic amber, with the description of a new species of Pantolyta Forster, 1856 (Hymenoptera, Diapriidae). Entomologica Fennica 10: 187 - 189. https: // doi. org / 10.33338 / ef. 84020" type="journal article" year="1999">Buhl, 1999</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11649767A87C2E8FA8D37A7" authority="(Buhl, 2002)" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Buhl" baseAuthorityYear="2002" box="[1017,1398,935,961]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="janzeni" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11649767A87C2E8FB3637A7" box="[1017,1229,935,961]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">Pantolyta janzeni</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11649767D9DC2E8FA9537A7" author="Buhl P. N." box="[1251,1390,935,961]" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" pagination="57 - 61" refId="ref14115" refString="Buhl P. N. 2002. On a Baltic amber collection of Platygastridae and Diapriidae (Hymenoptera). Entomologiske Meddelelser 70: 57 - 61." type="journal article" year="2002">Buhl, 2002</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D116497679C3C285FEBA3783" box="[189,321,970,997]" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11649767832C285FCBA3782" authority="(Jouault &amp; Nel, 2020)" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Jouault &amp; Nel" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[332,833,970,996]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perrichoti" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11649767832C285FDC13782" box="[332,570,970,996]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">Pantolyta perrichoti</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11649767B37C285FCC23782" author="Jouault C. &amp; Nel A." box="[585,825,970,996]" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" pagination="614 - 622" refId="ref15042" refString="Jouault C. &amp; Nel A. 2020. A new species of parasitoid wasps (Hymenoptera: Diapriidae: Belytinae) from Eocene Baltic amber. Palaeoentomology 3 (6): 614 - 622. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / palaeoentomology. 3.6.13" type="journal article" year="2020">Jouault &amp; Nel, 2020</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D11649767A36C285FC313783" box="[840,970,970,997]" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11649767D7FC285FF00306E" authority="Maneval, 1938" authorityName="Maneval" authorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="somnulenta">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11649767D7FC285FAFA3782" box="[1025,1281,970,996]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">Pantolyta somnulenta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11649767C76C285FF00306E" author="Maneval H." pageId="15" pageNumber="72" pagination="107 - 116" refId="ref15502" refString="Maneval H. 1938. Trois serphoides de l'ambre de la Baltique. Revue francaise d'Entomologie 5 (2): 107 - 116." type="journal article" year="1938">Maneval, 1938</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11649767874C2A2FE1A3061" authorityName="Buhl" authorityYear="1999" box="[266,481,1005,1031]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antiqua">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11649767874C2A2FE1A3061" box="[266,481,1005,1031]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">Pantolyta antiqua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the marginal vein as long as its distance from basal vein whereas it is distinctly shorter in 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD116497678CFC55EFCA0304D" authority="(Buhl 1999)" baseAuthorityName="Buhl" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[433,859,1041,1067]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantolyta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="augustinusii">
<emphasis id="B922590BD116497678CFC55EFD47304D" box="[433,700,1041,1067]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="72">Pantolyta augustinusii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11649767BB0C55EFCA9304D" author="Buhl P. N." box="[718,850,1041,1067]" pageId="15" pageNumber="72" pagination="187 - 189" refId="ref14061" refString="Buhl P. N. 1999. On a collection of Hymenoptera in Baltic amber, with the description of a new species of Pantolyta Forster, 1856 (Hymenoptera, Diapriidae). Entomologica Fennica 10: 187 - 189. https: // doi. org / 10.33338 / ef. 84020" type="journal article" year="1999">Buhl 1999</bibRefCitation>
)
